  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Cut the <strong>aubergines</strong> in half lengthways (including the stalks), then score the flesh in a criss-cross pattern, taking care not to cut through to the skin</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/indian-style-spiced-aubergine-tray-bake-with-spinach/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) the<strong> ginger</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>chopped ginger</strong> to a large bowl with the <strong>curry powder</strong>, <strong>half</strong> the <strong>natural yoghurt</strong> (save the rest for later!), a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and a generous pinch of<strong> salt</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/indian-style-spiced-aubergine-tray-bake-with-spinach/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Line a baking tray with <strong>non-stick baking paper </strong>and transfer the <strong>scored aubergine</strong>, cut side up, and spread most of the <strong>curry marinade</strong> all over them (save a little for later!)</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 4? Use 2 trays!</p><p>Put the tray<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> in the oven for an initial 10 min</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/indian-style-spiced-aubergine-tray-bake-with-spinach/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut the <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into small bite-sized pieces</p><p>Peel and chop the<strong> red onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into wedges</p><p>Crush the <strong>garlic</strong> with the side of a knife, keeping the skins on</p><p>Wash the <strong>spinach</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/indian-style-spiced-aubergine-tray-bake-with-spinach/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the aubergine has had an initial 10 min, add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong>, <strong>red onion wedges</strong> and<strong> crushed garlic </strong>to the tray<span class=\"text-danger\">[s] </span>with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Sprinkle over the <strong>ground turmeric </strong>and<strong> yellow mustard seeds</strong></p><p>Season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and stir it all together</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/indian-style-spiced-aubergine-tray-bake-with-spinach/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut the <strong>lemon<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into wedges</p><p>Squeeze half the<strong> lemon wedges</strong> over the <strong>potatoes</strong> and add the squeezed wedges to the tray<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> (save the remaining wedges for garnish)</p><p>Add in the <strong>reserved</strong> <strong>curry marinade </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Return the tray<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> to the oven for a further 30 min or until everything is cooked through and tender</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/indian-style-spiced-aubergine-tray-bake-with-spinach/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once everything's cooked through and tender, remove the tray<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> from the oven and top everything with the<strong> spinach </strong>then return the tray<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> to the oven for a further 5 min or until the spinach has wilted</p><p>Meanwhile, slice the<strong> red chilli<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> finely</p><p>Once the spinach has wilted, remove the tray<span class=\"text-danger\">[s] </span>from the oven<strong> </strong>and stir the it through the potatoes and onion wedges – this is your <strong>Indian-style spiced aubergine tray bake with spinach</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/indian-style-spiced-aubergine-tray-bake-with-spinach/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Indian-style spiced aubergine </strong>with the <strong>potato</strong>,<strong> spinach </strong>and<strong> onion wedges </strong>to the side</p><p>Dollop with the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>natural yoghurt</strong></p><p>Garnish with the<strong> sliced chilli</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>nigella seeds</strong> and <strong>lemon wedges</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
